edu.ucla.sspace.util
Interface MultiMap<K,V>

All Known Subinterfaces:
SortedMultiMap<K,V>
All Known Implementing Classes:
BoundedSortedMultiMap, HashMultiMap, TreeMultiMap
public interface MultiMap<K,V>

An object that maps a key to one or more values. A map cannot contain duplicate keys and each key cannot map to duplicate values.

See Also:
Map

remove

boolean remove(K key,
               V value)
Removes the specified mapping for a key if it is present. If the key is mapped to other values, it is retained, otherwise the key is removed from the map. This method provides a way to remove a specific mapping for a key without removing all other existing mappings.

Returns:
true if the specified mapping was removed

range

int range()
Returns the number of values maped to keys. Note that in the bijective case, this will equal the value returned by size(). However, in the case where a key is mapped to more than one value, this method will always return a value strictly larger than size().

Returns:
the number of values maped to keys
